{"lemma": "فَلَكٌ", "slug": "فَلَكٌ", "root": "ف.ل.ك", "root_slug": "ف-ل-ك", "root_link": "/words/roots/ف-ل-ك", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "فَلَك", "root": "فلك", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 2}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 7}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n34566", "n34567", "n34569", "n34570"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "orbit", "fa": "مدار", "ur": "مدار", "tr": "yörünge", "id": "orbit", "bn": "কক্ষপথ", "es": "órbita", "fr": "orbite", "de": "Umlaufbahn", "ru": "орбита", "zh": "轨道"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "orbit, rounded course", "examples": [{"text": "وَهُوَ ٱلَّذِي خَلَقَ ٱللَّيْلَ وَٱلنَّهَارَ وَٱلشَّمْسَ وَٱلْقَمَرَ كُلٌّ فِي فَلَكٍ يَسْبَحُونَ", "english": "And He is the One Who created the day and the night, the sun and the moon—each travelling in an orbit."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sphere"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sky, outer space, universe, (figurative) heaven"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "orb"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ellipsis of عِلْم الْفَلَك (ʕilm al-falak, “astronomy”)", "tags": ["abbreviation", "alt-of", "ellipsis"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "falak, ouroboros"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "ship", "examples": [{"text": "إِنَّ فِي خَلْقِ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالْأَرْضِ وَاخْتِلَافِ اللَّيْلِ وَالنَّهَارِ وَالْفُلْكِ الَّتِي تَجْرِي فِي الْبَحْرِ بِمَا يَنفَعُ النَّاسَ وَمَا أَنزَلَ اللَّهُ مِنَ السَّمَاءِ مِن مَّاءٍ فَأَحْيَا بِهِ الْأَرْضَ بَعْدَ مَوْتِهَا وَبَثَّ فِيهَا مِن كُلِّ دَابَّةٍ وَتَصْرِيفِ الرِّيَاحِ وَالسَّحَابِ الْمُسَخَّرِ بَيْنَ السَّمَاءِ وَالْأَرْضِ لَآيَاتٍ لِّقَوْمٍ يَعْقِلُونَ", "english": "Verily, in the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the alternation of night and day, and the ships that float in the sea with what benefits the people; and what Allah sends down from the sky of water and gives life with it(the water) to the earth after its death, and sisters in it (the earth) of all the moving creatures; and (in the) controlling of the wind and the clouds suspended between the sky and the earth are indeed signs for people using sense."}, {"text": "رَبُّكُمُ الَّذِي يُزْجِي لَكُمُ الْفُلْكَ فِي الْبَحْرِ لِتَبْتَغُوا مِن فَضْلِهِ إِنَّهُ كَانَ بِكُمْ رَحِيمًا"}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Belonging to the root ف ل ك (f l k).\n\nBelonging to the root ف ل ك (f l k). Perhaps, however, unrelated to etymology 1 and instead from Ancient Greek ἐφόλκιον (ephólkion). Nonetheless, it might be linked to Hebrew פֶּלֶךְ (pélekh, “spindle”), the relationship being \"being rounded\"."}, "ipa": ["/fa.lak/", "/fulk/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n34566", "headword_ar": "فلّك", "root": "flk", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, K,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tafokiykN", "text_ar": "تَفْكِيكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) said of a girl's breast,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It became round,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falokap", "text_ar": "فَلْكَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whirl"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a spindle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")], but less than is denoted by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nuhuwdN", "text_ar": "نُهُودٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[inf. n. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nahada", "text_ar": "نَهَدَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.]; (TA;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tfl~k", "text_ar": "تفلّك", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aflk", "text_ar": "افلك", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Th, O, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falaka", "text_ar": "فَلَكَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fl~kt", "text_ar": "فلّكت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) inf. n. as above, (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She became round in the breast;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falakato", "text_ar": "فَلَكَتْ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K, TA. [For the latter verb, the CK has"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falikat", "text_ar": "فَلِكَت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falokapN", "text_ar": "فَلْكَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", second sentence. ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~afokiyku", "text_ar": "التَّفْكِيكُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies The pastor's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making, of course hair"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hulob", "text_ar": "هُلْب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "),"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falokap", "text_ar": "فَلْكَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, T, S, O, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the spindle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, T, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and inserting it into the tongue of the young unweaned camel,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, T, S, O, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having perforated the tongue"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for that purpose"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (AA, T, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in order that he may not such:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, T, S, O, TA:) accord. to Lth,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fal~akotu AljadoYa", "text_ar": "فَلَّكْتُ الجَدْىَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I put a twig around the tongue of the kid in order that it might not suck:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but Az says that the right explanation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Altfkyk", "text_ar": "التفكيك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is that of AA [given above]. (TA.) [See also 4 in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jr", "text_ar": "جر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and 4 in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lhj", "text_ar": "لهج"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]       -A3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fl~k", "text_ar": "فلّك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n. as above,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a man)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "persisted,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "persevered,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laj~a", "text_ar": "لَجَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) in an affair; (K, TA;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aflk", "text_ar": "افلك", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)       -A4-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fl~kt", "text_ar": "فلّكت"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a bitch)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "desired copulation, and discharged blood from the womb;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AjElt", "text_ar": "اجعلت"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wHADt", "text_ar": "وحاضت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (O, K.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "O", "K", "TA", "Th", "AA", "T"]}, {"entry_id": "n34567", "headword_ar": "فُلْكٌ", "root": "flk", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A ship:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K, &c.:) [also particularly applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ark"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of Noah; as in the Kur-án vii. 62, &c.:] the word is generally thus only; but some say ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulukN", "text_ar": "فُلُكٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also, with two dammehs; and it is held that this may be the original form; and that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulokN", "text_ar": "فُلْكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may be a contraction, like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EunoqN", "text_ar": "عُنْقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is [of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gunuqN", "text_ar": "غُنُقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to Sb]: (MF, TA:) it is masc. and fem., (S, O, K, *) and sing. and pl., (S, O, K,) and Ibn-'Abbád says that it has"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuluwkN", "text_ar": "فُلُوكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also for a pl.: (O:) [it is said that] it may be sing., and in this case masc.; and pl., and in this case fem.: (IB, Msb:) [but see what here follows:] it occurs in the Kur-án in the following (and other) places: in xxvi. 119, &c.; where it is sing. and masc.: (S, O, TA:) and in [xvi. 14 and] xxxv. 13; where it is pl. [and fem.]: (TA:) and in ii. 159; where it is fem., and may be either pl. or sing.: it seems that, when it is sing., it is regarded as meaning the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "marokab", "text_ar": "مَرْكَب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and is therefore made masc.; or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "safiynap", "text_ar": "سَفِينَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and is therefore made fem.: (S, O, TA:) or, (K,) as Sb used to say, (S, O, TA,) the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulok", "text_ar": "فُلْك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that is a pl. [in meaning] is a broken pl. of that, (S, O, K, TA,) i. e. of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulok", "text_ar": "فُلْك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (IB, O, K, TA,) that is a sing. [in meaning]: and it is not like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljunubu", "text_ar": "الجُنُبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is sing. and pl. [in meaning], and the like thereof (S, O, K, TA) among substs., such as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlT~ifolu", "text_ar": "الطِّفْلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; (S, O, TA;) for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulokaAni", "text_ar": "فُلْكَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "has been heard from the Arabs as dual of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulokN", "text_ar": "فُلْكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "junubaAni", "text_ar": "جُنُبَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or the like] as dual of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "junubN", "text_ar": "جُنُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or the like]; and they say that what has not been dualized is not a pl. [form], but [is, or may be,] a homonym, and what has been dualized [is, or may be,] a pl. [form]: (MF, TA:) Sb then says in continuation, (TA,) for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuEolN", "text_ar": "فُعْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEalN", "text_ar": "فَعَلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "share in application to one thing [or meaning], as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEurobu", "text_ar": "العُرْبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEarabu", "text_ar": "العَرَبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, K, TA,) &c.; (S, O, TA;) and as it is allowable for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEalN", "text_ar": "فَعَلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to have for its pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuEolN", "text_ar": "فُعْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in the instance of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asadN", "text_ar": "اَسَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^usodN", "text_ar": "اُسْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", so too"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuEolN", "text_ar": "فُعْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may have for its pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuEolN", "text_ar": "فُعْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, O, K, TA.) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulokiY~N", "text_ar": "فُلْكِىٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a dial. var. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulokN", "text_ar": "فُلْكٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and Abu-d-Dardà read, [in the Kur x. 23,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kunotumo fiY A@lofulokiY~i", "text_ar": "كُنْتُمْ فِى ا@لْفُلْكِىِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "When ye are in the ships;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "where others read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fY Alfuloki", "text_ar": "فى الفُلْكِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and where the context shows that the pl. meaning is intended]. (IJ, TA.)       -A2-  [It may also be a pl. of the word next following]."}], "source_refs": ["MF", "TA", "S", "O", "K", "IB", "Msb"]}, {"entry_id": "n34569", "headword_ar": "فَلِكٌ", "root": "flk", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "A slave (AA, O)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having a buttock like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "falokap", "text_ar": "فَلْكَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whirl"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a spindle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, O, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in shape;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, O;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "resembling the Zenj;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) [for] the buttocks of the Zenj are round: (AA, O:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "large in the buttocks."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And (O, K) it is said to signify (O)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Thick,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "coarse of make, in the joints:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K:) and loose in the bones; (K;) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weak, loose in the bones, and flaccid;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "thus expl. by Ibn-'Abbád: (O:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having a pain in his patella"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY falokapi rukobatihi", "text_ar": "فِى فَلْ